ORBIT System Implementation Guide
This guide will help you set up the ORBIT system with Python Watchdog to automatically manage your knowledge architecture in Obsidian.
Step 1: Create Required Directories
First, let's make sure we have the right directory structure:

Create an ORBIT_work directory in your vault to store the scripts:
mkdir -p /Users/austinavent/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/Areas/DASR/ORBIT_work

Create a templates directory:
mkdir -p /Users/austinavent/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/Areas/DASR/templates


Step 2: Set Up the Template Files

Create the template creation script:

Save create-templates-improved.py to your ORBIT_work directory
Make sure the VAULT_PATH variable is set correctly


Run the template creation script:
cd /Users/austinavent/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/Areas/DASR/ORBIT_work
python create-templates-improved.py


Step 3: Set Up Domain Structure

Create the debugging script:

Save orbit-debug-improved.py to your ORBIT_work directory
Make sure the VAULT_PATH variable is set correctly


Run the script to create domain folders:
python orbit-debug-improved.py create-domains


Step 4: Set Up the Watchdog Script

Save the fixed watchdog script:

Save orbit-watchdog-fixed.py as orbit_watchdog.py in your ORBIT_work directory
Make sure the VAULT_PATH in the Config class is correct


Test the script by running it:
python orbit_watchdog.py


Step 5: Troubleshooting Existing Files
If you have issues with existing files, you can use the debugging script to fix them:

Check YAML syntax:
python orbit-debug-improved.py check-yaml --file path/to/file.md

Fix YAML issues:
python orbit-debug-improved.py fix-yaml --file path/to/file.md

Check overall structure:
python orbit-debug-improved.py check-structure


Common Issues and Solutions
Template Placeholders Not Being Replaced
If you see placeholders like PROJECT_TITLE or CURRENT_DATE in your notes:

Use the debug script to fix the file:
python orbit-debug-improved.py fix-yaml --file path/to/file.md

Or manually edit the file and replace placeholders with actual values.

Error: Cannot Determine Domain
If you see errors like "Cannot determine domain for orbit: X":

Make sure the domain is specified in the Config.DOMAINS dictionary
Add a domain property to your note's frontmatter
Make sure the orbit target exists or is a valid project name

Notes Not Moving to Correct Location
If notes aren't moving to the expected location:

Check if the project directory exists
Verify that the orbit relationships are correctly specified
Look for any error messages in the log

Usage Examples
Creating a New Note that Orbits a Project
md---
type: dust
created: 2025-04-16
domain: 200-Health
orbits: pelvic health
---

# Glute Bridges

Notes about glute bridges...
Creating a Project with Satellites
md---
type: project
created: 2025-04-16
domain: 200-Health
satellites:
  - feet
  - ankles
---

# Legs

Project about legs...
Creating a Note that Orbits Multiple Projects
md---
type: dust
created: 2025-04-16
domain: 200-Health
orbits:
  - pelvic health
  - core strength
direct: pelvic health
---

# Transverse Abdominis

Notes about the transverse abdominis muscle...
Starting the Watchdog Automatically
To have the watchdog start automatically when you open Obsidian, you can:
On macOS:
Create a Launch Agent:

Create a file at ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.orbit.watchdog.plist:

xml<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.orbit.watchdog</string>
    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/usr/bin/python3</string>
        <string>/Users/austinavent/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/Areas/DASR/ORBIT_work/orbit_watchdog.py</string>
    </array>
    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <true/>
    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>/Users/austinavent/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/Areas/DASR/ORBIT_work/orbit.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>/Users/austinavent/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/Areas/DASR/ORBIT_work/orbit-error.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>

Load the service:

bashlaunchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.orbit.watchdog.plist
Need Help?
If you encounter any issues:

Check the log file for error messages
Use the debugging tool to diagnose problems
Try recreating the templates and restarting the watchdog